Cell[TextData[{
 "Cells and substrate are fed to a steady-state chemostat (continuous \
stirred-tank bioreactor) where they react to form more cells. The cell \
concentration (dashed blue line) in the reactor is plotted versus the \
dilution rate ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["D", TraditionalForm]], "InlineMath",ExpressionUUID->
  "50302015-a467-41d0-ac91-ff3d9b914804"],
 ", which is the feed volumetric flow rate divided by the reactor volume. The \
concentration of unreacted substrate leaving the reactor (solid blue line) is \
also shown. The cell production rate (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"D", " ", 
    SubscriptBox["C", "cell"]}], TraditionalForm]], "InlineMath",
  ExpressionUUID->"1325f2e0-c227-439a-ad1a-5afb9afbeedb"],
 ") is the solid green line. Use sliders to change the feed substrate \
concentration, Monod constant, maximum growth rate and the cell death rate \
constant. Washout occurs at a high enough dilution rate that the cells are \
flushed out of the reactor and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["C", "cell"], "=", "0"}], TraditionalForm]], "InlineMath",
  ExpressionUUID->"679e1a22-7ee1-4bdb-b32e-618c8205fc3f"],
 ". Note that the scale on the right ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["y", TraditionalForm]], "InlineMath",ExpressionUUID->
  "b204bf61-1be9-4f21-9c85-12f49a7ef3c2"],
 " axis (green) changes as parameters change."
}], "Text",
 TaggingRules->{},
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.676211319303585*^9, 3.6762113758016014`*^9}, {
   3.676291834973717*^9, 3.67629183602815*^9}, {3.677351368567404*^9, 
   3.6773514266615486`*^9}, {3.680635383594265*^9, 3.680635385655469*^9}, {
   3.680635419096561*^9, 3.680635429314579*^9}, 3.681235521280263*^9, 
   3.681750464935113*^9, {3.68175070868814*^9, 3.6817507489614153`*^9}, {
   3.681750782701091*^9, 3.68175079438652*^9}, {3.681750831126965*^9, 
   3.681750831449415*^9}, 3.681750885138727*^9},
 CellID->197252680,ExpressionUUID->"727e70ae-41b3-43ba-b998-912005b2c116"]
}, Closed]],

